## File Organization

```
src/
├── core/           # Main SDK class
├── utils/          # Utility functions (safe-account, http-client)
├── config/         # Configuration (chains, endpoints, abis, constants)
│   ├── chains.ts   # Chain configurations
│   ├── endpoints.ts # API endpoints
│   ├── abis.ts     # Smart contract ABIs
│   └── constants.ts # Global constants
├── types/          # TypeScript type definitions
└── index.ts        # Public API exports
```

### File Purpose Guidelines

- **`src/core/`**: Main SDK class only. Keep business logic here.
- **`src/utils/`**: Reusable helper functions (Safe account logic, HTTP client, etc.)
- **`src/config/`**: Static configuration (chains, ABIs, endpoints, constants)
- **`src/types/`**: TypeScript interfaces and type definitions only
- **`examples/`**: Usage examples for different features

## Common Patterns

### Error Handling Pattern

```typescript
try {
  // Validate inputs first
  if (!userAddress || !chainId) {
    throw new Error("Missing required parameters");
  }

  // Execute logic
  const result = await someOperation();

  return {
    success: true,
    ...result,
  };
} catch (error) {
  throw new Error(`Operation failed: ${(error as Error).message}`);
}
```

### Guard Clauses Pattern

```typescript
async function deploySafe(userAddress: string, chainId: number) {
  // Guard clauses at the top
  if (!userAddress) {
    throw new Error("User address is required");
  }

  if (!isSupportedChain(chainId)) {
    throw new Error(`Unsupported chain ID: ${chainId}`);
  }

  // Main logic follows
  // ...
}
```

### Type Safety Pattern

```typescript
// Always validate and type external data
function validateAddress(address: unknown): Address {
  if (typeof address !== "string" || !address.startsWith("0x")) {
    throw new Error("Invalid address format");
  }
  return address as Address;
}
```

